commit.message:
Relax upper bound of dependencies

Allow the following,
- base-4.20.*
- hspec-2.12.*
- deepseq-1.6.*
- text-2.1.*
Remove allow-newer in cabal.project
Fix the compatible ghc range for the test-suite
Use ghc-9.8.1 in the CI
CI: Use GHC Nightlies
CI: Add GHC 9.8.0

Improve Cabal files

- Remove redundant “default-language”
- Change “extra-source-files” to “extra-doc-files” (warning from Cabal 3.10).
- Remove unused “DeriveAnyClass” and “TemplateHaskell” default extensions.
- Add “tasty” upper bound (fix Cabal warning).
- Improve “ghc-options” for benchmarks, as per tasty-bench recommendations.
Update CI (9.2, 9.6)

Optimize Addr# literals: no inline & size reduction (#106)

* Do not inline Addr# literals

These literals are huge and will be duplicated at each call site of
functions using them.

See:
- https://github.com/haskell/core-libraries-committee/issues/130
- https://gitlab.haskell.org/ghc/ghc/-/issues/22949
- https://gitlab.haskell.org/ghc/ghc/-/merge_requests/9958/

* Span Addr# literals accross multiple lines

This facilitate the use of text editors.

Note: there is an issue using CPP with multi-lines Addr# literal.
See: https://downloads.haskell.org/ghc/latest/docs/users_guide/phases.html#cpp-and-string-gaps

* Compress Addr# literals

Unicode code points are divided in 17 planes (numbered 0 to 16):
- plane 0 is BMP,
- planes 1 to 3 contains supplementary chars,
- planes 4 to 13 are unassigned,
- plane 14 contains supplementary chars,
- planes 15 to 16 are private use area.

So we can divide the literals in 2:
- planes 0 to 3
- plane 14
and use default values for the rest of the planes.

* Improve predicates depending on generalCategory

* Update comments on base Unicode versions

* Update benchmark results
